Subject: Colorado Access - Discovery Wkshop 2.0
Description: Met with Janet and reviewed the deck similar to what Matt and I presented to CareOregon - medicaid focus where we used Rx Claims and Eligibility files to locate the most complex members via high Rx utilization, large prescriber count, high prevalence of chronic conditions.   Janet is very impressed with our approach to targeting members and could see us a partner to target the complex members as part of their ACO to work on the behavioral health focus as well as Diabetes, Asthma, and COPD.  She also brought up the idea of us helping them secure contracting eith the State Medicaid group since most of the ROI towards overcoming SDOH, lowering cost of care, closing care gaps, etc would go to the medicaid organization  Next STeps: Send NDA, complete initial analysis so we can provide estimated budget numbers, send details about compliance, share strategies around targeting transient populations

Commercial only plan, majority of the business is ASO. Provides same type of services for fully insured and ASO ?	Plan?s objective is to delight and retain employers  ?	Parent company Fairview also owns a PBM ?Clearscript?. 80% of the members use this PBM ?	Clearscript has MTM program with many rules and triggers ?	Is also looking at specialty drugs and site of care  ?	Clearscript engages with members via phone or video ?	Pharmacists reach out to the providers  ?	*Potential opportunity for pharmacy at home/AdhereRx  ?	Not sure that Kristi has buying decision power. She had a hard stop for another meeting.  ?	Will reconnect to further discuss AdhereRx.
